About this item

  • Dried mango slices are a fun tropical treat and true delight. This conveniently packed, top quality dried mango snack lets you enjoy the delicious, sweet taste of real mangoes at home or on the go with our convenient, resealable pouch.
  • All-natural unsweetened dried mango slices let you enjoy the all-natural sweetness and juicy taste of one of the sweetest fruits on earth. No Sugar added, non-GMO and preservative free. Just the sweet goodness you crave and deserve.
  • Dried mango can be just as sweet and delicious as candy, yet it offers lots of healthy and nutritional benefits for a guilt free treat. Dried mango is packed with antioxidants, rich in dietary fiber and provides vitamins A and C.
  • Mango becomes even sweeter and tastier when dried. Enjoy our highest quality dried mango conveniently packed in a resealable pouch. Dried mango should be stored in an air tight container for extended shelf life and freshness.
  • Enjoy these dried mangoes slices as a convenient ready to eat snack or as part of a delicious dessert. Try these great dried mango slices in curries, chutneys, compotes, yoghurts, cereals, muesli, cakes and more.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzes reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      3.0 out of 5 stars Gross but lots of it
      Reviewed in the United States on May 20, 2021
      Verified Purchase
      Edit: Bumping up to a 3. I bought it again as I couldn't remember if i did or not the first go around. Much better this time. The taste and texture are there, so I would say the first one was semi-bad.
      We'll see if a third time around will take this to a 4.

      I get that dried fruit generally isn't top tier...as in sellable as fresh due to imperfections. While the flavor is strong, it's definitely the flavor of extremely overripe, bordering on rotten mangoes. I have a bag of Mariani dried mangoes on my desk and aside from some flavor that can be identified as mango, they taste almost nothing alike.

      It's quite moist though I wonder if that will start molding. I've scratched off some of the dark spots and am currently watching to see if the dark spots start spreading.

      Now if overripe mango is your thing, assuming this doesn't mold, this might be what you're looking for.
